<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-11-22T08:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-11-22T08:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">763.72119 P 43/956: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Special Representative</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_HCEM1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">House</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-11-22T13:00:00+00:00">November 22, 1918—1 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received November 22—10 a.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>141. From <persName corresp="#p_GJC1">Grew</persName>. I have been
                            informed that the French Government is taking the necessary step to
                            place the Hotel Crillon at <pb facs="0195" n="125" xml:id="pg_125"/> our
                            disposal. Ambassador <persName corresp="#p_SWG1">Sharp</persName> is
                            attending to all of these negotiations and will no doubt report direct
                            on terms thereof. We are making satisfactory progress with physical
                            organization of offices in quarters previously occupied by Red Cross at
                            4 Place de la Concorde.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Edward House</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>